sapTlsManagedVlanListTable.name: sapTlsManagedVlanListTable
sapTlsManagedVlanListTable.description: This table is used only for SAPs that are part of a management VPLS. It indicates for each SAP the ranges of associated VLANs that will be affected when the SAP changes state.

sapTlsManagedVlanListEntry.name: sapTlsManagedVlanListEntry
sapTlsManagedVlanListEntry.description: Each row specifies a range of VLANS associated with a SAP of a MVPLS. Ranges may contains overlapping sections only for Mvpls SAPs that belong to the same service.

sapTlsMvplsMinVlanTag.name: sapTlsMvplsMinVlanTag
sapTlsMvplsMinVlanTag.description: The value of sapTlsMvplsMinVlanTag specifies the left bound (i.e. min. value) of a range of VLANs that are associated with the Mvpls SAP. sapTlsMvplsMinVlanTag must be smaller than (or equal to) sapTlsMvplsMaxVlanTag. Special values are: 0: this value is reserved for the null tag. 4095: this value denotes the default SAP.

sapTlsMvplsMaxVlanTag.name: sapTlsMvplsMaxVlanTag
sapTlsMvplsMaxVlanTag.description: The value of sapTlsMvplsMaxVlanTag specifies the right bound (i.e. max. value) of a range of VLANs that are associated with the Mvpls SAP. Special values are: 0: this value is reserved for the null tag. 4095: this value denotes the default SAP.

sapTlsMvplsRowStatus.name: sapTlsMvplsRowStatus
sapTlsMvplsRowStatus.description: The value of sapTlsMvplsRowStatus specifies the status of this row. The only values supported during a set operation are 'createAndGo' and 'destroy'. A row (i.e. a range of VLAN tags) can be destroyed only if there are no SAPs defined in regular VPLSses in this range.

sapAntiSpoofTable.name: sapAntiSpoofTable
sapAntiSpoofTable.description: The sapAntiSpoofTable contains information about anti-spoofing filters on a SAP.

sapAntiSpoofIpAddress.name: sapAntiSpoofIpAddress
sapAntiSpoofIpAddress.description: The value of sapAntiSpoofIpAddress indicates the IP address for which this table entry contains information.

sapAntiSpoofMacAddress.name: sapAntiSpoofMacAddress
sapAntiSpoofMacAddress.description: The value of sapAntiSpoofMacAddress indicates the MAC address for which this table entry contains information.

sapStaticHostTable.name: sapStaticHostTable
sapStaticHostTable.description: The sapStaticHostTable is used to configure static hosts on a SAP.

sapStaticHostEntry.name: sapStaticHostEntry
sapStaticHostEntry.description: Each row entry represents information on a statically configured host. Entries can be created and deleted via SNMP SET operations.

sapStaticHostRowStatus.name: sapStaticHostRowStatus
sapStaticHostRowStatus.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostRowStatus controls the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

sapStaticHostIpAddress.name: sapStaticHostIpAddress
sapStaticHostIpAddress.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostIpAddress specifies the IP address associated with this static host. The value 0.0.0.0 indicates that no host IP address is specified.

sapStaticHostMacAddress.name: sapStaticHostMacAddress
sapStaticHostMacAddress.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostMacAddress specifies the MAC address associated with this static host. The value 0:0:0:0:0:0 indicates that no host MAC address is specified.

sapStaticHostSubscrIdent.name: sapStaticHostSubscrIdent
sapStaticHostSubscrIdent.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostSubscrIdent specifies the subscriber identification for this static host.

sapStaticHostSubProfile.name: sapStaticHostSubProfile
sapStaticHostSubProfile.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostSubProfile specifies the subscriber profile for this static host. The specified subscriber profile needs to exists in the TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB::tmnxSubProfileTable.

sapStaticHostSlaProfile.name: sapStaticHostSlaProfile
sapStaticHostSlaProfile.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostSlaProfile specifies the SLA profile for this static host. The specified SLA profile needs to exists in the TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB::tmnxSLAProfileTable.

sapStaticHostShcvOperState.name: sapStaticHostShcvOperState
sapStaticHostShcvOperState.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostShcvOperState gives the state of the subscriber host connectivity check for this static host.

sapStaticHostShcvChecks.name: sapStaticHostShcvChecks
sapStaticHostShcvChecks.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostShcvChecks specifies the number of connectivity checks for this static host.

sapStaticHostShcvReplies.name: sapStaticHostShcvReplies
sapStaticHostShcvReplies.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostShcvReplies specifies the number of host replies for this static host.

sapStaticHostShcvReplyTime.name: sapStaticHostShcvReplyTime
sapStaticHostShcvReplyTime.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostShcvReplyTime gives the timestamp of the last successful connectivity check for this static host.

sapStaticHostDynMacAddress.name: sapStaticHostDynMacAddress
sapStaticHostDynMacAddress.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostDynMacAddress gives the MAC address learned via ARP in case this is an IP-only static host (sapStaticHostMacAddress is set to 0:0:0:0:0:0). The value 0:0:0:0:0:0 indicates that no MAC address is learned yet.

sapStaticHostRetailerSvcId.name: sapStaticHostRetailerSvcId
sapStaticHostRetailerSvcId.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostRetailerSvcId indicates the service ID of the retailer VPRN service to which this static host belongs. When this object is non zero, the static host belongs to a retailer VPRN.

sapStaticHostRetailerIf.name: sapStaticHostRetailerIf
sapStaticHostRetailerIf.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostRetailerIf indicates the interface index of the retailer VPRN interface to which this static host belongs. When this object is non zero, the static host belongs to a retailer VPRN.

sapStaticHostFwdingState.name: sapStaticHostFwdingState
sapStaticHostFwdingState.description: The value of sapStaticHostFwdingState indicates the forwarding state of this static host. When the value is 'outOfService', host traffic is not forwarded. When it is 'inService', host traffic is forwarded.

sapStaticHostAncpString.name: sapStaticHostAncpString
sapStaticHostAncpString.description: The value of sapStaticHostAncpString specifies the ancp-string associated to this SAP host.

sapStaticHostSubIdIsSapId.name: sapStaticHostSubIdIsSapId
sapStaticHostSubIdIsSapId.description: The value of the object sapStaticHostSubIdIsSapId specifies whether the SAP-id is taken as subscriber identification for this static host.

sapStaticHostAppProfile.name: sapStaticHostAppProfile
sapStaticHostAppProfile.description: The value of sapStaticHostAppProfile specifies the application profile for this static host. The specified application profile needs to exist in the TIMETRA-BSX-MIB::tmnxBsxAppProfTable.

sapStaticHostIntermediateDestId.name: sapStaticHostIntermediateDestId
sapStaticHostIntermediateDestId.description: The value of sapStaticHostIntermediateDestId specifies to which intermediate destination (for example a DSLAM) this host belongs.

sapTlsDhcpInfoTable.name: sapTlsDhcpInfoTable
sapTlsDhcpInfoTable.description: sapTlsDhcpInfoTable contains DHCP information related to a TLS SAP. This table complements sapTlsInfoTable, and contains an entry for each Tls SAP. Rows in this table are created and deleted automatically by the system.

sapTlsDhcpInfoEntry.name: sapTlsDhcpInfoEntry
sapTlsDhcpInfoEntry.description: DHCP specific information for a TLS SAP.

sapTlsDhcpAdminState.name: sapTlsDhcpAdminState
sapTlsDhcpAdminState.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpAdminState specifies the overall enable/disable state of all DHCP related actions on this Sap. The value 'disabled' allows the user to configure individual DHCP commands but administratively disable them.

sapTlsDhcpDescription.name: sapTlsDhcpDescription
sapTlsDhcpDescription.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpDescription specifies a user provided description for DHCP on this Sap. It consists of any printable, seven-bit ASCII characters up to 80 characters in length.

sapTlsDhcpSnoop.name: sapTlsDhcpSnoop
sapTlsDhcpSnoop.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpSnoop specifies the enable/disable state for DHCP snooping on this Sap. Note that in order for snooping to be enabled the object sapTlsDhcpAdminState must also have the value enabled.

sapTlsDhcpLeasePopulate.name: sapTlsDhcpLeasePopulate
sapTlsDhcpLeasePopulate.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpLeasePopulate specifies the maximum number of DHCP lease states allowed on this SAP.

sapTlsDhcpOperLeasePopulate.name: sapTlsDhcpOperLeasePopulate
sapTlsDhcpOperLeasePopulate.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpOperLeasePopulate indicates the number of DHCP lease states currently allocated on this SAP.

sapTlsDhcpInfoAction.name: sapTlsDhcpInfoAction
sapTlsDhcpInfoAction.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpInfoAction specifies the DHCP option reforwarding policy: 'replace' - replace existing information with configured information 'drop' - discard messages with existing relay information if the option-82 information is also present. 'keep' - retain the existing relay information.

sapTlsDhcpCircuitId.name: sapTlsDhcpCircuitId
sapTlsDhcpCircuitId.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpCircuitId specifies whether or not the circuit-id suboption is present, and if it is present what information goes in it: - 'none' the circuit-id suboption will not be part of the information option (Option 82). - 'asciiTuple' the ASCII-encoded concatenated tuple consisting of the - access-node-identifier - service-id - interface-name is used. - 'vlanAsciiTuple' the format will include VLAN-id and dot1p bits in addition to what is included in ascii-tuple already. The format is supported on dot1q and qinq encapsulated ports only. Thus, when the option 82 bits are stripped, dot1p bits will be copied to the Ethernet header of an outgoing packet.

sapTlsDhcpRemoteId.name: sapTlsDhcpRemoteId
sapTlsDhcpRemoteId.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpRemoteId specifies what information goes into the remote-id suboption in the DHCP Relay packet. If the value of this object is set to 'none', the remote-id suboption will not be part of the information option (Option 82). If the value of this object is set to 'mac', the MAC address of the remote end is encoded in the suboption. If the value of this object is set to 'remote-id', sapTlsDhcpRemoteIdString will represent the remote-id. By default, the remote-id value is none.

sapTlsDhcpRemoteIdString.name: sapTlsDhcpRemoteIdString
sapTlsDhcpRemoteIdString.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpRemoteIdString specifies the remote-id. This object exists only if sapTlsDhcpRemoteId has a value of 'remote-id'.

sapTlsDhcpProxyAdminState.name: sapTlsDhcpProxyAdminState
sapTlsDhcpProxyAdminState.description: The value of sapTlsDhcpProxyAdminState specifies the desired administrative state of the proxy server on this interface. Note that in order for the proxy server to be enabled, the value of sapTlsDhcpAdminState must also be 'enabled'.

sapTlsDhcpProxyServerAddr.name: sapTlsDhcpProxyServerAddr
sapTlsDhcpProxyServerAddr.description: The value of sapTlsDhcpProxyServerAddr specifies the IP address which will be used as the source address of the emulated DHCP server in the context of this VPLS SAP. This address is mandatory for the proxy server capability and it should be in the context of the subnet represented by this VPLS.

sapTlsDhcpProxyLeaseTime.name: sapTlsDhcpProxyLeaseTime
sapTlsDhcpProxyLeaseTime.description: The value of sapTlsDhcpProxyLeaseTime specifies in seconds how long a DHCP client is allowed to use the offered IP address. Value 0 means the lease time provided by a RADIUS or an upstream DHCP server will not be overridden. A lease time of 7 days is used when RADIUS does not provide a lease time.

sapTlsDhcpProxyLTRadiusOverride.name: sapTlsDhcpProxyLTRadiusOverride
sapTlsDhcpProxyLTRadiusOverride.description: The value of sapTlsDhcpProxyLTRadiusOverride specifies whether or not the lease time provided by the RADIUS server is presented to the DHCP client. By default the proxy-server will always make use of sapTlsDhcpProxyLeaseTime, regardless of what lease time information is provided from the RADIUS server. When sapTlsDhcpProxyLTRadiusOverride is set to 'true', the proxy-server will use the lease time information provided by the RADIUS server, regardless of the configured one.

sapTlsDhcpVendorIncludeOptions.name: sapTlsDhcpVendorIncludeOptions
sapTlsDhcpVendorIncludeOptions.description: The value of sapTlsDhcpVendorIncludeOptions specifies what is encoded in the Alcatel vendor specific sub-option of option 82. The value of this object is only used when sapTlsDhcpInfoAction is 'replace'.

sapTlsDhcpVendorOptionString.name: sapTlsDhcpVendorOptionString
sapTlsDhcpVendorOptionString.description: The value of sapTlsDhcpVendorOptionString specifies the string that goes into the Alcatel vendor specific sub-option of option 82. This string is only used when sapTlsDhcpInfoAction is set to 'replace'.

sapTlsDhcpStatsTable.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsTable
sapTlsDhcpStatsTable.description: sapTlsDhcpStatsTable contains DHCP statistics related to a TLS SAP. This table complements sapTlsInfoTable, and contains an entry for each Tls SAP. Rows in this table are created and deleted automatically by the system.

sapTlsDhcpStatsEntry.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsEntry
sapTlsDhcpStatsEntry.description: DHCP statistics for a TLS SAP.

sapTlsDhcpStatsClntSnoopdPckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsClntSnoopdPckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsClntSnoopdPckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsClntSnoopdPckts indicates the number of DHCP client packets that have been snooped on this SAP.

sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrSnoopdPckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrSnoopdPckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrSnoopdPckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrSnoopdPckts indicates the number of DHCP server packets that have been snooped on this SAP.

sapTlsDhcpStatsClntForwdPckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsClntForwdPckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsClntForwdPckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsClntForwdPckts indicates the number of DHCP client packets that have been forwarded on this SAP.

sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrForwdPckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrForwdPckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrForwdPckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrForwdPckts indicates the number of DHCP server packets that have been forwarded on this SAP.

sapTlsDhcpStatsClntDropdPckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsClntDropdPckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsClntDropdPckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsClntDropdPckts indicates the number of DHCP client packets that have been dropped on this SAP.

sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrDropdPckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrDropdPckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrDropdPckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsSrvrDropdPckts indicates the number of DHCP server packets that have been dropped on this SAP.

sapTlsDhcpStatsClntProxRadPckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsClntProxRadPckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsClntProxRadPckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsClntProxRadPckts indicates the number of DHCP client packets that have been proxied on this SAP based on data received from a RADIUS server.

sapTlsDhcpStatsClntProxLSPckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsClntProxLSPckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsClntProxLSPckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsClntProxLSPckts indicates the number of DHCP client packets that have been proxied on this SAP based on a lease state. The lease itself can have been obtained from a DHCP or RADIUS server. This is the so called lease split functionality.

sapTlsDhcpStatsGenReleasePckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsGenReleasePckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsGenReleasePckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsGenReleasePckts indicates the number of DHCP RELEASE messages spoofed on this SAP to the DHCP server.

sapTlsDhcpStatsGenForceRenPckts.name: sapTlsDhcpStatsGenForceRenPckts
sapTlsDhcpStatsGenForceRenPckts.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpStatsGenForceRenPckts indicates the number of DHCP FORCERENEW messages spoofed on this SAP to the DHCP clients.

sapTlsDhcpLeaseStateTable.name: sapTlsDhcpLeaseStateTable
sapTlsDhcpLeaseStateTable.description: sapTlsDhcpLeaseStateTable contains DHCP lease state info for a TLS SAP. This table complements sapTlsInfoTable, and contains an entry for each Tls SAP. Rows in this table are created and deleted automatically by the system. The content of this table is moved to the svcDhcpLeaseStateTable.

sapTlsDhcpLeaseStateEntry.name: sapTlsDhcpLeaseStateEntry
sapTlsDhcpLeaseStateEntry.description: DHCP Lease State information on a TLS SAP.

sapTlsDhcpLseStateCiAddr.name: sapTlsDhcpLseStateCiAddr
sapTlsDhcpLseStateCiAddr.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpLseStateCiAddr indicates the IP address of the DHCP lease state.

sapTlsDhcpLseStateChAddr.name: sapTlsDhcpLseStateChAddr
sapTlsDhcpLseStateChAddr.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpLseStateChAddr indicates the MAC address of the DHCP lease state.

sapTlsDhcpLseStateRemainLseTime.name: sapTlsDhcpLseStateRemainLseTime
sapTlsDhcpLseStateRemainLseTime.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpLseStateRemainLseTime indicates the remaining lease time of the Ip address of the DHCP lease state. This object was made obsolete in the 4.0 release.

sapTlsDhcpLseStateOption82.name: sapTlsDhcpLseStateOption82
sapTlsDhcpLseStateOption82.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpLseStateOption82 indicates the content of the Option82 for this DHCP lease state. This object was made obsolete in the 4.0 release.

sapTlsDhcpLseStatePersistKey.name: sapTlsDhcpLseStatePersistKey
sapTlsDhcpLseStatePersistKey.description: The value of the object sapTlsDhcpLseStatePersistKey indicates a key value that can be used to track this lease state in the persistence file. This object was made obsolete in the 4.0 release.

sapPortIdIngQosSchedStatsTable.name: sapPortIdIngQosSchedStatsTable
sapPortIdIngQosSchedStatsTable.description: The sapPortIdIngQosSchedStatsTable contains ingress QoS queue SAP statistics. This table is used when the SAP is a CCAG or LAG in 'link' mode, or an APS.

sapPortIdIngQosSchedStatsEntry.name: sapPortIdIngQosSchedStatsEntry
sapPortIdIngQosSchedStatsEntry.description: Each entry represents the ingress statistics about a specific SAP's QoS queue. Entries are created when a scheduler policy is applied to a SAP.

sapPortIdIngQosSchedName.name: sapPortIdIngQosSchedName
sapPortIdIngQosSchedName.description: The value of sapPortIdIngQosSchedName is used as an index of the ingress QoS scheduler of this SAP.

sapPortIdIngPortId.name: sapPortIdIngPortId
sapPortIdIngPortId.description: The value of sapPortIdIngPortId is used as an index of the ingress QoS scheduler of this SAP. When the SAP is an aps/ccag/lag in 'link' mode, this object is the TmnxPortID of the member-port on which the scheduler is applied.

sapPortIdIngQosSchedFwdPkts.name: sapPortIdIngQosSchedFwdPkts
sapPortIdIngQosSchedFwdPkts.description: The value of sapPortIdIngQosSchedFwdPkts indicates the number of forwarded packets, as determined by the SAP ingress scheduler policy, offered by the Pchip to the Qchip.

sapPortIdIngQosSchedFwdOctets.name: sapPortIdIngQosSchedFwdOctets
sapPortIdIngQosSchedFwdOctets.description: The value of sapPortIdIngQosSchedFwdOctets indicates the number of forwarded octets,as determined by the SAP ingress scheduler policy, offered by the Pchip to the Qchip.

sapPortIdIngQosSchedCustId.name: sapPortIdIngQosSchedCustId
sapPortIdIngQosSchedCustId.description: The value of sapPortIdIngQosSchedCustId indicates the Customer ID for the associated service.

sapPortIdEgrQosSchedStatsTable.name: sapPortIdEgrQosSchedStatsTable
sapPortIdEgrQosSchedStatsTable.description: The sapPortIdEgrQosSchedStatsTable contains egress QoS queue SAP statistics. This table is used when the SAP is a CCAG or LAG in 'link' mode, or an APS.

sapPortIdEgrQosSchedStatsEntry.name: sapPortIdEgrQosSchedStatsEntry
sapPortIdEgrQosSchedStatsEntry.description: Each entry represents the egress statistics about a specific SAP's QoS queue. Entries are created when a scheduler policy is applied to a SAP.

sapPortIdEgrQosSchedName.name: sapPortIdEgrQosSchedName
sapPortIdEgrQosSchedName.description: The value of sapPortIdEgrQosSchedName is used as an index of the egress QoS scheduler of this SAP.

sapPortIdEgrPortId.name: sapPortIdEgrPortId
sapPortIdEgrPortId.description: The value of sapPortIdEgrPortId is used as an index of the egress QoS scheduler of this SAP. When the SAP is an aps/ccag/lag in 'link' mode, this object is the TmnxPortID of the member-port on which the scheduler is applied.

sapPortIdEgrQosSchedFwdPkts.name: sapPortIdEgrQosSchedFwdPkts
sapPortIdEgrQosSchedFwdPkts.description: The value of sapPortIdEgrQosSchedFwdPkts indicates the number of forwarded packets, as determined by the SAP egress scheduler policy, offered by the Pchip to the Qchip.

sapPortIdEgrQosSchedFwdOctets.name: sapPortIdEgrQosSchedFwdOctets
sapPortIdEgrQosSchedFwdOctets.description: The value of sapPortIdEgrQosSchedFwdOctets indicates the number of forwarded octets,as determined by the SAP egress scheduler policy, offered by the Pchip to the Qchip.

sapPortIdEgrQosSchedCustId.name: sapPortIdEgrQosSchedCustId
sapPortIdEgrQosSchedCustId.description: The value of sapPortIdEgrQosSchedCustId indicates the Customer ID for the associated service.

sapIngQosQueueInfoTable.name: sapIngQosQueueInfoTable
sapIngQosQueueInfoTable.description: This table is used to override the base parameters of a queue, as defined in the associated SAP ingress QoS policy.

sapIngQosQueueInfoEntry.name: sapIngQosQueueInfoEntry
sapIngQosQueueInfoEntry.description: Override values for the specified SAP ingress QoS queue. These values override the corresponding ones specified in the associated SAP ingress QoS policy.

sapIngQosQId.name: sapIngQosQId
sapIngQosQId.description: The value of sapIngQosQId indicates the ID of the queue whose parameters are to be overridden.

sapIngQosQRowStatus.name: sapIngQosQRowStatus
sapIngQosQRowStatus.description: The value of sapIngQosQRowStatus controls the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

sapIngQosQLastMgmtChange.name: sapIngQosQLastMgmtChange
sapIngQosQLastMgmtChange.description: The value of sapIngQosQLastMgmtChange indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the last management change of any writable object of this row.

sapIngQosQOverrideFlags.name: sapIngQosQOverrideFlags
sapIngQosQOverrideFlags.description: The value of sapIngQosQOverrideFlags specifies the set of attributes whose values have been overridden via management on this queue. Clearing a given flag will return the corresponding overridden attribute to the value defined on the SAP's ingress QoS policy.

sapIngQosQCBS.name: sapIngQosQCBS
sapIngQosQCBS.description: The value of sapIngQosQCBS specifies the amount of reserved buffer space (in kilo bytes) for this queue.

sapIngQosQMBS.name: sapIngQosQMBS
sapIngQosQMBS.description: The value of sapIngQosQMBS specifies the maximum amount of buffer space (in kilo bytes) allowed for this queue.

sapIngQosQHiPrioOnly.name: sapIngQosQHiPrioOnly
sapIngQosQHiPrioOnly.description: The value of sapIngQosQHiPrioOnly specifies the percentage of buffer space for this queue, used exclusively by high priority packets.

sapIngQosQCIRAdaptation.name: sapIngQosQCIRAdaptation
sapIngQosQCIRAdaptation.description: The value of sapIngQosQCIRAdaptation specifies the criteria to use to compute the operational CIR value for this queue, while maintaining a minimum offset.

sapIngQosQPIRAdaptation.name: sapIngQosQPIRAdaptation
sapIngQosQPIRAdaptation.description: The value of sapIngQosQPIRAdaptation specifies the criteria to use to compute the operational PIR value for this queue, while maintaining a minimum offset.

sapIngQosQAdminPIR.name: sapIngQosQAdminPIR
sapIngQosQAdminPIR.description: The value of sapIngQosQAdminPIR specifies the desired PIR value for this queue.

sapIngQosQAdminCIR.name: sapIngQosQAdminCIR
sapIngQosQAdminCIR.description: The value of sapIngQosQAdminCIR specifies the desired CIR value for this queue.

sapEgrQosQueueInfoTable.name: sapEgrQosQueueInfoTable
sapEgrQosQueueInfoTable.description: This table is used to override the base parameters of a queue, as defined in the associated SAP egress QoS policy.

sapEgrQosQueueInfoEntry.name: sapEgrQosQueueInfoEntry
sapEgrQosQueueInfoEntry.description: Override values for the specified SAP egress QoS queue. These values override the corresponding ones specified in the associated SAP egress QoS policy.

sapEgrQosQId.name: sapEgrQosQId
sapEgrQosQId.description: The value of sapEgrQosQId indicates the ID of the queue whose parameters are to be overridden.

sapEgrQosQRowStatus.name: sapEgrQosQRowStatus
sapEgrQosQRowStatus.description: The value of sapEgrQosQRowStatus controls the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

sapEgrQosQLastMgmtChange.name: sapEgrQosQLastMgmtChange
sapEgrQosQLastMgmtChange.description: The value of sapEgrQosQLastMgmtChange indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the last management change of any writable object of this row.

sapEgrQosQOverrideFlags.name: sapEgrQosQOverrideFlags
sapEgrQosQOverrideFlags.description: The value of sapEgrQosQOverrideFlags specifies the set of attributes whose values have been overridden via management on this queue. Clearing a given flag will return the corresponding overridden attribute to the value defined on the SAP's ingress QoS policy.

sapEgrQosQCBS.name: sapEgrQosQCBS
sapEgrQosQCBS.description: The value of sapEgrQosQCBS specifies the amount of reserved buffer space (in kilo bytes) for this queue.

sapEgrQosQMBS.name: sapEgrQosQMBS
sapEgrQosQMBS.description: The value of sapEgrQosQMBS specifies the maximum amount of buffer space (in kilo bytes) allowed for this queue.

sapEgrQosQHiPrioOnly.name: sapEgrQosQHiPrioOnly
sapEgrQosQHiPrioOnly.description: The value of sapEgrQosQHiPrioOnly specifies the percentage of buffer space for this queue, used exclusively by high priority packets.

sapEgrQosQCIRAdaptation.name: sapEgrQosQCIRAdaptation
sapEgrQosQCIRAdaptation.description: The value of sapEgrQosQCIRAdaptation specifies the criteria to use to compute the operational CIR value for this queue, while maintaining a minimum offset.

sapEgrQosQPIRAdaptation.name: sapEgrQosQPIRAdaptation
sapEgrQosQPIRAdaptation.description: The value of sapEgrQosQPIRAdaptation specifies the criteria to use to compute the operational PIR value for this queue, while maintaining a minimum offset.

sapEgrQosQAdminPIR.name: sapEgrQosQAdminPIR
sapEgrQosQAdminPIR.description: The value of sapEgrQosQAdminPIR specifies the desired PIR value for this queue.

sapEgrQosQAdminCIR.name: sapEgrQosQAdminCIR
sapEgrQosQAdminCIR.description: The value of sapEgrQosQAdminCIR specifies the desired CIR value for this queue.

sapEgrQosQAvgOverhead.name: sapEgrQosQAvgOverhead
sapEgrQosQAvgOverhead.description: The value of sapEgrQosQAvgOverhead specifies the encapsulation overhead, in hundredths of a percent, used to translate packet-based rate to frame-based rate and vice versa.

sapIngQosSchedInfoTable.name: sapIngQosSchedInfoTable
sapIngQosSchedInfoTable.description: This table is used to override the base parameters of a virtual scheduler, as defined in the associated SAP ingress scheduler policy.

sapIngQosSchedInfoEntry.name: sapIngQosSchedInfoEntry
sapIngQosSchedInfoEntry.description: Override values for the specified SAP ingress virtual scheduler. These values override the corresponding ones specified in the associated SAP ingress scheduler policy.

sapIngQosSName.name: sapIngQosSName
sapIngQosSName.description: The value of sapIngQosSName indicates the name of the virtual scheduler whose parameters are to be overridden.

sapIngQosSRowStatus.name: sapIngQosSRowStatus
sapIngQosSRowStatus.description: The value of sapIngQosSRowStatus controls the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

sapIngQosSLastMgmtChange.name: sapIngQosSLastMgmtChange
sapIngQosSLastMgmtChange.description: The value of sapIngQosSLastMgmtChange indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the last management change of any writable object of this row.

sapIngQosSOverrideFlags.name: sapIngQosSOverrideFlags
sapIngQosSOverrideFlags.description: The value of sapIngQosSOverrideFlags specifies the set of attributes whose values have been overridden via management on this virtual scheduler. Clearing a given flag will return the corresponding overridden attribute to the value defined on the SAP's ingress scheduler policy.

sapIngQosSPIR.name: sapIngQosSPIR
sapIngQosSPIR.description: The value of sapIngQosSPIR specifies the desired PIR value for this virtual scheduler.

sapIngQosSCIR.name: sapIngQosSCIR
sapIngQosSCIR.description: The value of sapIngQosSCIR specifies the desired CIR value for this virtual scheduler.

sapIngQosSSummedCIR.name: sapIngQosSSummedCIR
sapIngQosSSummedCIR.description: The value of sapIngQosSSummedCIR specifies if the CIR should be used as the summed CIR values of the children schedulers or queues. If set to 'true', the applicable scheduler CIR (sapIngQosSCIR) loses its meaning.

sapEgrQosSchedInfoTable.name: sapEgrQosSchedInfoTable
sapEgrQosSchedInfoTable.description: This table is used to override the base parameters of a virtual scheduler, as defined in the associated SAP egress scheduler policy.

sapEgrQosSchedInfoEntry.name: sapEgrQosSchedInfoEntry
sapEgrQosSchedInfoEntry.description: Override values for the specified SAP egress virtual scheduler. These values override the corresponding ones specified in the associated SAP egress scheduler policy.

sapEgrQosSName.name: sapEgrQosSName
sapEgrQosSName.description: The value of sapEgrQosSName indicates the name of the virtual scheduler whose parameters are to be overridden.

sapEgrQosSRowStatus.name: sapEgrQosSRowStatus
sapEgrQosSRowStatus.description: The value of sapEgrQosSRowStatus controls the creation and deletion of rows in this table.

sapEgrQosSLastMgmtChange.name: sapEgrQosSLastMgmtChange
sapEgrQosSLastMgmtChange.description: The value of sapEgrQosSLastMgmtChange indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the last management change of any writable object of this row.

sapEgrQosSOverrideFlags.name: sapEgrQosSOverrideFlags
sapEgrQosSOverrideFlags.description: The value of sapEgrQosSOverrideFlags specifies the set of attributes whose values have been overridden via management on this virtual scheduler. Clearing a given flag will return the corresponding overridden attribute to the value defined on the SAP's egress scheduler policy.

sapEgrQosSPIR.name: sapEgrQosSPIR
sapEgrQosSPIR.description: The value of sapEgrQosSPIR specifies the desired PIR value for this virtual scheduler.

sapEgrQosSCIR.name: sapEgrQosSCIR
sapEgrQosSCIR.description: The value of sapEgrQosSCIR specifies the desired CIR value for this virtual scheduler.

sapEgrQosSSummedCIR.name: sapEgrQosSSummedCIR
sapEgrQosSSummedCIR.description: The value of sapEgrQosSSummedCIR specifies if the CIR should be used as the summed CIR values of the children schedulers or queues. If set to 'true', the applicable scheduler CIR (sapEgrQosSCIR) loses its meaning.

sapSubMgmtInfoTable.name: sapSubMgmtInfoTable
sapSubMgmtInfoTable.description: A table that contains SAP subscriber management information.

sapSubMgmtInfoEntry.name: sapSubMgmtInfoEntry
sapSubMgmtInfoEntry.description: Subscriber management specific information about a SAP.

sapSubMgmtAdminStatus.name: sapSubMgmtAdminStatus
sapSubMgmtAdminStatus.description: The value of sapSubMgmtAdminStatus specifies whether enhanced subscriber management is enabled on this SAP.

sapSubMgmtDefSubProfile.name: sapSubMgmtDefSubProfile
sapSubMgmtDefSubProfile.description: The value of sapSubMgmtDefSubProfile specifies the default subscriber profile applicable on this SAP. The corresponding profile is defined in TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB::tmnxSubProfileTable. A value of 'default' is not allowed for this object.

sapSubMgmtDefSlaProfile.name: sapSubMgmtDefSlaProfile
sapSubMgmtDefSlaProfile.description: The value of sapSubMgmtDefSlaProfile specifies the default SLA profile applicable on this SAP. The corresponding profile is defined in TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB::tmnxSLAProfileTable.

sapSubMgmtSubIdentPolicy.name: sapSubMgmtSubIdentPolicy
sapSubMgmtSubIdentPolicy.description: The value of sapSubMgmtSubIdentPolicy specifies the subscriber identification policy applicable on this SAP. The corresponding policy is defined in TIMETRA-SUBSCRIBER-MGMT-MIB::tmnxSubIdentPolicyTable.

sapSubMgmtSubscriberLimit.name: sapSubMgmtSubscriberLimit
sapSubMgmtSubscriberLimit.description: The value of sapSubMgmtSubscriberLimit specifies the maximum number of subscribers allowed for this SAP. If the value is 0, there is no limit. Only if the value is 1, the 'single-sub-parameters' defined with objects sapSubMgmtProfiledTrafficOnly, sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSubProf and sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSlaProf are meaningful.

sapSubMgmtProfiledTrafficOnly.name: sapSubMgmtProfiledTrafficOnly
sapSubMgmtProfiledTrafficOnly.description: The value of sapSubMgmtProfiledTrafficOnly specifies whether only profiled traffic is applicable for this SAP. If set to 'true', all SAP queues will be deleted. The value of this object is only meaningful if sapSubMgmtSubscriberLimit is set to 1.

sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSubIdent.name: sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSubIdent
sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSubIdent.description: The value of sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSubIdent specifies the subscriber identification applicable on this SAP for all non-subscriber traffic. The value of this object is only meaningful if sapSubMgmtSubscriberLimit is set to 1.

sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSubProf.name: sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSubProf
sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSubProf.description: The value of sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSubProf specifies the subscriber profile applicable on this SAP for all non-subscriber traffic. The value of this object is only meaningful if sapSubMgmtSubscriberLimit is set to 1.

sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSlaProf.name: sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSlaProf
sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSlaProf.description: The value of sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficSlaProf specifies the SLA profile applicable on this SAP for all non-subscriber traffic. The value of this object is only meaningful if sapSubMgmtSubscriberLimit is set to 1.

sapSubMgmtMacDaHashing.name: sapSubMgmtMacDaHashing
sapSubMgmtMacDaHashing.description: The value of sapSubMgmtMacDaHashing specifies whether subscriber traffic egressing a LAG SAP has its egress LAG link selected by a function of the MAC destination address instead of subscriber id. The value of this object is only meaningful if sapSubMgmtAdminStatus is set to 'enabled' and can only be configured for TLS services.

sapSubMgmtDefSubIdent.name: sapSubMgmtDefSubIdent
sapSubMgmtDefSubIdent.description: The value of sapSubMgmtDefSubIdent specifies what is used as the default subscriber identification applicable on this SAP. This value is used in case no other source (like Radius) provides a subscriber identification string. If the value of this objects is set to 'useSapId', the SAP-id is used as the default subscriber identification string. In this case, sapSubMgmtDefSubIdentString must contain the empty string. If the value of this object is set to 'useString', the value of sapSubMgmtDefSubIdentString is used as the default subscriber identification string. In this case, an empty sapSubMgmtDefSubIdentString means that there is no default subscriber identification configured.

sapSubMgmtDefSubIdentString.name: sapSubMgmtDefSubIdentString
sapSubMgmtDefSubIdentString.description: The value of sapSubMgmtDefSubIdentString specifies the default subscriber identification string applicable on this SAP.

sapSubMgmtDefAppProfile.name: sapSubMgmtDefAppProfile
sapSubMgmtDefAppProfile.description: The value of sapSubMgmtDefAppProfile specifies the default application profile applicable on this SAP. The corresponding profile is defined in TIMETRA-BSX-MIB::tmnxBsxAppProfTable.

sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficAppProf.name: sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficAppProf
sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficAppProf.description: The value of sapSubMgmtNonSubTrafficAppProf specifies the application profile applicable on this SAP for all non-subscriber traffic. The value of this object is only meaningful if sapSubMgmtSubscriberLimit is set to 1.

sapTlsMstiTable.name: sapTlsMstiTable
sapTlsMstiTable.description: This table contains Multiple Spanning Tree Instance information for the SAP. Each management VPLS running MSTP can have upto 15 MSTI. An entry in this table is automatically created when a tlsMstiEntry is created.

sapTlsMstiEntry.name: sapTlsMstiEntry
sapTlsMstiEntry.description: Information about a specific MSTI for a SAP.

sapTlsMstiPriority.name: sapTlsMstiPriority
sapTlsMstiPriority.description: The value of the object sapTlsMstiPriority specifies the value of the port priority field which is contained in the most significant 4 bits of the 16-bit Port ID associated with this SAP and MSTI. As only the most significant 4 bits of the value are used, the actual value of this object is limited to multiples of 16: e.g. the agent rounds down the value to one of: 0, 16, 32, .. , 224, 240.

sapTlsMstiPathCost.name: sapTlsMstiPathCost
sapTlsMstiPathCost.description: The value of the object sapTlsMstiPathCost specifies the contribution of this port to the MSTI path cost of paths towards the spanning tree regional root which include this port.

sapTlsMstiLastMgmtChange.name: sapTlsMstiLastMgmtChange
sapTlsMstiLastMgmtChange.description: The value of the object sapTlsMstiLastMgmtChange indicates the value of sysUpTime at the time of the most recent management-initiated change to this SAP MSTI information.

sapTlsMstiPortRole.name: sapTlsMstiPortRole
sapTlsMstiPortRole.description: sapTlsMstiPortRole indicates the current role of the sap in the MSTI as defined by the Spanning Tree Protocol.

sapTlsMstiPortState.name: sapTlsMstiPortState
sapTlsMstiPortState.description: The value of the object sapTlsMstiPortState indicates the port's current state as defined by application of the Spanning Tree Protocol. This state controls what action a port takes on reception of a frame. If the bridge has detected a port that is malfunctioning it will place that port into the 'broken' state.

sapTlsMstiDesignatedBridge.name: sapTlsMstiDesignatedBridge
sapTlsMstiDesignatedBridge.description: The value of the object sapTlsMstiDesignatedBridge indicates the Bridge Identifier of the bridge which this port considers to be the Designated Bridge for this port's segment for this MSTI.

sapTlsMstiDesignatedPort.name: sapTlsMstiDesignatedPort
sapTlsMstiDesignatedPort.description: The value of the object sapTlsMstiDesignatedPort indicates the Port Identifier of the port on the Designated Bridge for this port's segment for this MSTI.

sapIpipeInfoTable.name: sapIpipeInfoTable
sapIpipeInfoTable.description: A table that contains IPIPE specific SAP information.

sapIpipeInfoEntry.name: sapIpipeInfoEntry
sapIpipeInfoEntry.description: IPIPE specific information about a SAP.

sapIpipeCeInetAddressType.name: sapIpipeCeInetAddressType
sapIpipeCeInetAddressType.description: The value of the object sapIpipeCeInetAddressType specifies the addresstype of the local end host IP of an IPIPE.

sapIpipeCeInetAddress.name: sapIpipeCeInetAddress
sapIpipeCeInetAddress.description: The type of this address is determined by the value of the sapIpipeCeInetAddressType object. This object specifies the IPv4 address of the local end host of an IPIPE.

sapIpipeMacRefreshInterval.name: sapIpipeMacRefreshInterval
sapIpipeMacRefreshInterval.description: The value of sapIpipeMacRefreshInterval specifies the interval between successive attempts to refresh the MAC address of the CE device associated with an Ethernet ipipe SAP. If no other event (such as reception of an ARP request from the CE) occurs that would refresh the MAC address before the end of the interval, an ARP request will be originated from the IPIPE SAP.

sapIpipeMacAddress.name: sapIpipeMacAddress
sapIpipeMacAddress.description: The value of the object sapIpipeMacAddress specifies the MAC address of an IPIPE Ethernet SAP.

sapIpipeArpedMacAddress.name: sapIpipeArpedMacAddress
sapIpipeArpedMacAddress.description: The value of the object sapIpipeArpedMacAddress indicates the MAC address of the local end host.

sapIpipeArpedMacAddressTimeout.name: sapIpipeArpedMacAddressTimeout
sapIpipeArpedMacAddressTimeout.description: The value of the object sapIpipeArpedMacAddressTimeout indicates the number of seconds to wait for the sapIpipeArpedMacAddress to be re-refreshed.

sapTodMonitorTable.name: sapTodMonitorTable
sapTodMonitorTable.description: This table contains information on configurable objects on SAP level, that can be modified by a scheduled policy.

sapTodMonitorEntry.name: sapTodMonitorEntry
sapTodMonitorEntry.description: Information about ToD policy modifiable config data for a SAP.

sapCurrentIngressIpFilterId.name: sapCurrentIngressIpFilterId
sapCurrentIngressIpFilterId.description: The value of the object sapCurrentIngressIpFilterId indicates the index in the tIPFilterTable corresponding to the ingress filter applied on this SAP, or zero if no filter is currently active. The active filter may deviate from sapIngressIpFilterId in case it is overruled by a ToD Suite policy.

sapCurrentIngressIpv6FilterId.name: sapCurrentIngressIpv6FilterId
sapCurrentIngressIpv6FilterId.description: The value of the object sapCurrentIngressIpv6FilterId indicates the index in the tIPv6FilterTable corresponding to the ingress Ipv6 filter applied on this SAP, or zero if no filter is currently active. The active filter may deviate from sapIngressIpv6FilterId in case it is overruled by a ToD Suite policy.

sapCurrentIngressMacFilterId.name: sapCurrentIngressMacFilterId
sapCurrentIngressMacFilterId.description: The value of the object sapCurrentIngressMacFilterId indicates the index in the tMacFilterTable corresponding to the ingress Mac filter applied on this SAP, or zero if no filter is currently active. The active filter may deviate from sapIngressMacFilterId in case it is overruled by a ToD Suite policy.

sapCurrentIngressQosSchedPlcy.name: sapCurrentIngressQosSchedPlcy

The active policy may deviate from sapIngressQosSchedulerPolicy in case it is overruled by a ToD Suite policy defined on this SAP, or on the multi-service this SAP belongs to.

sapCurrentEgressIpFilterId.name: sapCurrentEgressIpFilterId

sapIntendedIngressIpFilterId.name: sapIntendedIngressIpFilterId
sapIntendedIngressIpFilterId.description: The value of the object sapIntendedIngressIpFilterId indicates the index in the tIPFilterTable corresponding to the ingress IP filter that should be applied on this SAP. If it deviates from sapCurrentIngressIpFilterId, this means that there was a problem when trying to activate this filter. It can only deviate when using ToD Suites for the SAP. When the ToD Suites decides that a new filter must be applied, it will try to do this. If it fails, the current and intended field are not equal.

sapIntendedEgressQosSchedPlcy.name: sapIntendedEgressQosSchedPlcy
sapIntendedEgressQosSchedPlcy.description: The value of the object sapIntendedEgressQosSchedPlcy indicates the index in the tSapEgressTable corresponding to the Egress Qos Scheduler policy that should be applied on this SAP. If it deviates from sapCurrentEgressQosSchedPlcy, this means that there was a problem when trying to activate this filter. It can only deviate when using ToD Suites for the SAP. sapIngrQosPlcyStatsTable.name: sapIngrQosPlcyStatsTable
sapIngrQosPlcyStatsTable.description: A table that contains Ingress Qos policy related statistics for a SAP.

sapIngrQosPlcyStatsEntry.name: sapIngrQosPlcyStatsEntry
sapIngrQosPlcyStatsEntry.description: Statistics about a specific Ingress Qos Policy applied on a specific SAP.

sapIgQosPlcyId.name: sapIgQosPlcyId
sapIgQosPlcyId.description: The value of the object sapIgQosPlcyId indicates the row index in the tSapIngressTable corresponding to this ingress QoS policy, or one if no policy is specified.

sapIgQosPlcyDroppedHiPrioPackets.name: sapIgQosPlcyDroppedHiPrioPackets
sapIgQosPlcyDroppedHiPrioPackets.description: The value of the object sapIgQosPlcyDroppedHiPrioPackets indicates the number of high priority packets, as determined by the SAP ingress QoS policy, dropped by the Qchip due to: MBS exceeded, buffer pool limit exceeded, etc.

sapIgQosPlcyDroppedHiPrioOctets.name: sapIgQosPlcyDroppedHiPrioOctets
sapIgQosPlcyDroppedHiPrioOctets.description: The value of the object sapIgQosPlcyDroppedHiPrioOctets indicates the number of high priority octets, as determined by the SAP ingress QoS policy, dropped by the Qchip due to: MBS exceeded, buffer pool limit exceeded, etc.

sapIgQosPlcyDroppedLoPrioPackets.name: sapIgQosPlcyDroppedLoPrioPackets
sapIgQosPlcyDroppedLoPrioPackets.description: The value of the object sapIgQosPlcyDroppedLoPrioPackets indicates the number of low priority packets, as determined by the SAP ingress QoS policy, dropped by the Qchip due to: MBS exceeded, buffer pool limit exceeded, etc.

sapIgQosPlcyDroppedLoPrioOctets.name: sapIgQosPlcyDroppedLoPrioOctets
sapIgQosPlcyDroppedLoPrioOctets.description: The value of the object sapIgQosPlcyDroppedLoPrioOctets indicates the number of low priority octets, as determined by the SAP ingress QoS policy, dropped by the Qchip due to: MBS exceeded, buffer pool limit exceeded, etc.

sapIgQosPlcyForwardedInProfPackets.name: sapIgQosPlcyForwardedInProfPackets
sapIgQosPlcyForwardedInProfPackets.description: The value of the object sapIgQosPlcyForwardedInProfPackets indicates the number of in-profile packets (rate below CIR) forwarded by the ingress Qchip.

sapIgQosPlcyForwardedInProfOctets.name: sapIgQosPlcyForwardedInProfOctets
sapIgQosPlcyForwardedInProfOctets.description: The value of the object sapIgQosPlcyForwardedInProfOctets indicates the number of in-profile octets (rate below CIR) forwarded by the ingress Qchip.

sapIgQosPlcyForwardedOutProfPackets.name: sapIgQosPlcyForwardedOutProfPackets

sapIgQosPlcyForwardedOutProfOctets.name: sapIgQosPlcyForwardedOutProfOctets
sapIgQosPlcyForwardedOutProfOctets.description: The value of the object sapIgQosPlcyForwardedOutProfOctets indicates the number of out-of-profile octets (rate above CIR) forwarded by the ingress Qchip.

sapCemPayloadSize.name: sapCemPayloadSize
sapCemPayloadSize.description: This object specifies the payload size (in bytes) of packets transmitted to the Packet Service Network (PSN) by the CEM SAP. This determines the size of the data that will be transmitted over the service. As well, if the size of the data received is not consistent with the payload size then the packet is considered malformed. Default value depends on the CEM SAP endpoint type (sapCemEndpointType), and if applicable, the number of timeslots (sapCemBitrate): --------------------------------------------------------- | Endpoint Type | Timeslots | Default payload size | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'unstructuredE1' | n/a | 256 bytes | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'unstructuredT1' | n/a | 192 bytes | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'unstructuredE3' | n/a | 1024 bytes | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'unstructuredT3' | n/a | 1024 bytes | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'nxDS0' (E1/T1) | N = 1 | 64 bytes | | +-----------+----------------------- | | N = 2..4 | N x 32 bytes | | +-----------+----------------------- | | N = 5..15 | N x 16 bytes | | +-----------+----------------------- | | N >= 16 | N x 8 bytes | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'nxDS0WithCas' (E1)| N | N x 16 bytes | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'nxDS0WithCas' (T1)| N | N x 24 bytes | --------------------------------------------------------- For all endpoint types except for 'nxDS0WithCas', valid payload size range is from the default (in the table above) to 2048 bytes. For 'nxDS0WithCas', sapCemPayloadSize divide by the number of timeslots (sapCemBitrate) must be an integer factor of the number of frames per trunk multiframe (i.e. 16 for E1 trunk and 24 for T1 trunk). For '1xDS0', sapCemPayloadSize must be a multiple of 2. For 'NxDS0', where N > 1, sapCemPayloadSize must be a multiple of the number of timeslots (sapCemBitrate). For 'unstructuredE1', 'unstructuredT1', 'unstructuredE3' and 'unstructuredT3', sapCemPayloadSize must be a multiple of 32 bytes. Configuring sapCemPayloadSize and sapCemJitterBuffer to values that result in less than 2 packet buffers or greater than 32 packet buffer is not allowed. Setting this object to 0 sets it back to the default value.

sapCemJitterBuffer.name: sapCemJitterBuffer
sapCemJitterBuffer.description: This object specifies the jitter buffer size in milliseconds (ms). Default value depends on the CEM SAP endpoint type (sapCemEndpointType), and if applicable, the number of timeslots (sapCemBitrate): --------------------------------------------------------- | Endpoint Type | Timeslots | Default jitter buf. | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'unstructuredE1' | n/a | 5 ms | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'unstructuredT1' | n/a | 5 ms | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'unstructuredE3' | n/a | 5 ms | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'unstructuredT3' | n/a | 5 ms | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'nxDS0' (E1/T1) | N = 1 | 32 ms | | +-----------+----------------------- | | N = 2..4 | 16 ms | | +-----------+----------------------- | | N = 5..15 | 8 ms | | +-----------+----------------------- | | N >= 16 | 5 ms | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'nxDS0WithCas' (E1)| N | 8 ms | ---------------------+-----------+----------------------- | 'nxDS0WithCas' (T1)| N | 12 ms | --------------------------------------------------------- Configuring sapCemPayloadSize and sapCemJitterBuffer to values that result in less than 2 packet buffers or greater than 32 packet buffers is not allowed. The valid range is 1 to 250 ms. Setting this object to 0 sets it back to the default value.

sapCemStatsEgressESs.name: sapCemStatsEgressESs

sapCemStatsEgressSESs.name: sapCemStatsEgressSESs

sapCemStatsEgressFailureCounts.name: sapCemStatsEgressFailureCounts

sapCemStatsEgressUnderrunCounts.name: sapCemStatsEgressUnderrunCounts
